==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Slew
<hw>Slew</hw> <pr>(sl⟦oomac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Slough</er> a wet place.]</ety> <def>A wet place; a river
inlet.</def></p>

<p><q>The praire round about is wet, at times almost marshy, especially
at the borders of the great reedy <qex>slews</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>T.
Roosevelt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

